{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"sourceId":"bookOfFiveRings","displayName":"Book of Five Rings (Musashi)","type":"quotes","language":"English","edition":"Public Domain Translation","primaryCategory":"Philosophy & Thought","subcategory":"Strategy","audienceTags":["strategy","discipline"],"sortPriority":47,"itemCount":30,"supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true,"browseOrder":"sequence","groupingLevels":["scroll","section"],"groupingLabels":["Scroll","Section"],"dataPath":"Data/Collections/Musashi_FiveRings.json","version":"1.0"},"data":[{"id":"fiverings-earth-1","text":"Accepting this, my intention is for all warriors whether commanders or common soldiers, to carry out the principles of strategy.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Earth Scroll, Section 1","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Earth","section":"1"},"sequenceIndex":0},{"id":"fiverings-earth-2","text":"The Way of the warrior is the resolute acceptance of death.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Earth Scroll, Section 2","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Earth","section":"2"},"sequenceIndex":1},{"id":"fiverings-earth-3","text":"Do not let the enemy see your spirit.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Earth Scroll, Section 3","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Earth","section":"3"},"sequenceIndex":2},{"id":"fiverings-earth-4","text":"Think of strategy on a large scale and a small scale.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Earth Scroll, Section 4","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Earth","section":"4"},"sequenceIndex":3},{"id":"fiverings-earth-5","text":"Know the ways of all professions.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Earth Scroll, Section 5","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Earth","section":"5"},"sequenceIndex":4},{"id":"fiverings-earth-6","text":"Distinguish between gain and loss in worldly matters.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Earth Scroll, Section 6","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Earth","section":"6"},"sequenceIndex":5},{"id":"fiverings-earth-7","text":"Develop intuitive judgment and understanding for everything.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Earth Scroll, Section 7","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Earth","section":"7"},"sequenceIndex":6},{"id":"fiverings-earth-8","text":"Perceive those things which cannot be seen.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Earth Scroll, Section 8","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Earth","section":"8"},"sequenceIndex":7},{"id":"fiverings-earth-9","text":"Pay attention even to trifles.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Earth Scroll, Section 9","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Earth","section":"9"},"sequenceIndex":8},{"id":"fiverings-earth-10","text":"Do nothing which is of no use.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Earth Scroll, Section 10","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Earth","section":"10"},"sequenceIndex":9},{"id":"fiverings-water-1","text":"In strategy your spiritual bearing must not be any different from normal. Both in fighting and in everyday life you should be determined though calm.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Water Scroll, Section 1","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Water","section":"1"},"sequenceIndex":10},{"id":"fiverings-water-2","text":"With your eyes, you should look neither down nor up, and your eyes should not shift. Keep your eyes steady without moving them.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Water Scroll, Section 2","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Water","section":"2"},"sequenceIndex":11},{"id":"fiverings-water-3","text":"The spirit of defeating a man is the same for ten million men as it is for one man.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Water Scroll, Section 3","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Water","section":"3"},"sequenceIndex":12},{"id":"fiverings-water-4","text":"Move quickly, using the advantage of your position. Use the spirit of 'one step ahead.'","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Water Scroll, Section 4","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Water","section":"4"},"sequenceIndex":13},{"id":"fiverings-water-5","text":"In all fighting, the eyes are used to perceive the enemy's spirit and see the advantage.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Water Scroll, Section 5","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Water","section":"5"},"sequenceIndex":14},{"id":"fiverings-fire-1","text":"When you decide to attack, keep calm and dash in quickly, forestalling the enemy. Attack with a feeling of constantly crushing the enemy, from first to last.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Fire Scroll, Section 1","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Fire","section":"1"},"sequenceIndex":15},{"id":"fiverings-fire-2","text":"To cut and to slash are two different things. Cutting is decisive and confident. Slashing is more of a tentative blow.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Fire Scroll, Section 2","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Fire","section":"2"},"sequenceIndex":16},{"id":"fiverings-fire-3","text":"In strategy it is important to see distant things as if they were close and to take a distanced view of close things.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Fire Scroll, Section 3","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Fire","section":"3"},"sequenceIndex":17},{"id":"fiverings-fire-4","text":"Know your enemy's capabilities, and use them against him.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Fire Scroll, Section 4","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Fire","section":"4"},"sequenceIndex":18},{"id":"fiverings-fire-5","text":"In large-scale strategy, the superior position is won not only in battle but through the force of character.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Fire Scroll, Section 5","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Fire","section":"5"},"sequenceIndex":19},{"id":"fiverings-wind-1","text":"In martial arts you must study other schools to understand their advantages and disadvantages.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Wind Scroll, Section 1","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Wind","section":"1"},"sequenceIndex":20},{"id":"fiverings-wind-2","text":"The way of the warrior is to master the virtue of his weapons.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Wind Scroll, Section 2","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Wind","section":"2"},"sequenceIndex":21},{"id":"fiverings-wind-3","text":"A warrior with weak spirit, whatever his technical skill, will be defeated in battle.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Wind Scroll, Section 3","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Wind","section":"3"},"sequenceIndex":22},{"id":"fiverings-wind-4","text":"One who knows the way broadly will see it in all things. This principle governs all professions.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Wind Scroll, Section 4","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Wind","section":"4"},"sequenceIndex":23},{"id":"fiverings-wind-5","text":"In all arts and skills there is the spirit, and the expression of the spirit is the practice of the art.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Wind Scroll, Section 5","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Wind","section":"5"},"sequenceIndex":24},{"id":"fiverings-void-1","text":"The Void is that which has no beginning and no end.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Void Scroll, Section 1","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Void","section":"1"},"sequenceIndex":25},{"id":"fiverings-void-2","text":"Without knowledge of the Void, you cannot know the way.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Void Scroll, Section 2","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Void","section":"2"},"sequenceIndex":26},{"id":"fiverings-void-3","text":"In the Void there is virtue, and the reality of the warrior's spirit.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Void Scroll, Section 3","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Void","section":"3"},"sequenceIndex":27},{"id":"fiverings-void-4","text":"Polish your wisdom: learn public justice, distinguish between good and evil, study the ways of different arts one by one.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Void Scroll, Section 4","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Void","section":"4"},"sequenceIndex":28},{"id":"fiverings-void-5","text":"With your spirit settled, accumulate practice day by day, and hour by hour. Polish the twofold spirit heart and mind, and sharpen the twofold gaze perception and sight. When your spirit is not in the least clouded, when the clouds of bewilderment clear away, there is the true Void.","author":"Miyamoto Musashi","source":"Book of Five Rings — The Void Scroll, Section 5","tags":["philosophy","strategy","japanese","bushido","language:english","collection:fiverings"],"groups":{"scroll":"Void","section":"5"},"sequenceIndex":29}]}